LAB ACTION PLAN FOR WEEK 5

Docker:

Working with Docker CLI Commands:

Docker CLI Commands with redis

Step 1: Pull the redis Image
docker pull redis

Step 2: Run a Redis Container
docker run --name my-redis -d redis

Step 3: Check Running Containers
docker ps

Step 4: Access Redis and open CLI inside container
docker exec -it my-redis redis-cli
SET name "Alice"
GET name

Step 5: Stop the Redis Container
docker stop my-redis

Step 6: Restart the Redis Container
docker start my-redis

Step 7: Remove the Redis Container permanently
docker rm my-redis

Step 8: Remove the Redis Image from local system
docker rmi redis

2. Working with Docker file

Step 1: Set Up Your Folder (Windows)
cd /c/DockerProjects/Redis
git init

Docker Commands (Step-by-step):

1. Build a new Docker image using Dockerfile in current folder and tag it
docker build -t redisnew  .

2. Run container from redisnew image in background and name it
docker run --name myredisnew -d redisnew

3. List running containers
docker ps

4. Stop the container by name
docker stop myredisnew

5. Login to Docker Hub account
docker login

6. List all containers including stopped ones
docker ps -a

7. Create a new Docker image snapshot from container ID
docker commit 0e993d2009a1 budarajumadhurika/redis1

8. List all local Docker images
docker images

9. Push the image to Docker Hub repository
docker push budarajumadhurika/redis1

10. Remove container using ID
docker rm 0e993d2009a1

11. Remove Docker image from local system
docker rmi budarajumadhurika/redis1

12. Show all containers to confirm changes
docker ps -a

13. Logout of Docker Hub
docker logout

14. Pull the image back from Docker Hub
docker pull budarajumadhurika/redis1

15. Run a new container from pulled image and name it
docker run --name myredis -d budarajumadhurika/redis1

16. Open Redis CLI inside running container
docker exec -it myredis redis-cli
SET name "Abcdef"
GET name

19. Exit Redis CLI
exit

20. List all containers and check status
docker ps -a

21. Stop the container by name
docker docker stop myredis

22. Remove container using ID
docker rm 50a6e4a9c326

23. List Docker images
docker images

24. Remove redis image from local again
docker rmi budarajumadhurika/redis1

Step 3: Remove login credentials (optional)
docker logout
